TITLE UURef for Transient Values
UUREF FOR TRANSIENT VALUES
When a value changes frequently and you don't want a re-render on every update (e.g., mouse trackers, intervals, transient flags), store it in useRef IO useState. Keep component state for UI; use refs for temporary DOM-adjacent values. Updating a ref does not trigger a re-render. 
Incorrect (renders every update): 
CODE tsx 451CHARS
Correct (no re-render for tracking): 
